snippet.title: CBC News: The National | Return to B.C. flood zones, Kids COVID-19 vaccines, Throne Speech
snippet.description:
Nov. 23, 2021 | More B.C. residents return to see what’s left of their homes and communities after the devastating flooding as officials are questioned about the lack of a widespread warning. The first COVID-19 vaccines for kids are administered in Ontario. Plus, At Issue breaks down the Trudeau government’s third throne speech. 

00:00 The National for Nov. 23, 2021
00:57 More rain on the way for B.C. flood zones
04:20 Travellers may have been mistakenly ticketed
04:55 Calls for B.C. to use phone alerts
08:38 Storm slams into Atlantic Canada
09:54 COVID-19 vaccine rollout for kids
12:17 Birth services suspended in Yellowknife
12:43 Paper questions breast cancer screening 
15:07 Throne speech lays out familiar priorities
18:18 Women held in ISIS camp back in Canada
18:52 Driver charged in Wisconsin parade attack
19:15 45 people killed in Bulgaria bus crash 
19:37 Tension on Russia-Ukrainian border
22:51 At Issue: Throne speech messaging
29:23 At Issue: Opposition reaction to throne speech
34:15 Family returns to flood B.C. home 
38:52 Returning to the office after the pandemic
41:39 The Moment
